title: Led Zeppelin - 1977.05.21 Houston, Tx (Remastered)
description:
Led Zeppelin - 1977.05.21 Houston, Texas (Remastered)   

Led Zeppelin
1977-05-21
The Summit
Houston, Texas
"The Dragon Snake Remastered" 

Remastered** by thir13en:
"It was cool. Maybe some have made too big a deal over how good the source sounds, but overall a quality listen. I did to it what I thought sounded best. It's still a little heavy on the rhythm section and the mid-range orgy between Plant and Page continues, but to me an improvement on the original. Check it out, or don't, your call.

Source: 
Incomplete excellent soundboard recording. 184 minutes.

Details: 
The recording is a very good balanced professional board tape.

Comments:
The brightest star of this concert is John Bonham who continued to deliver a 
high level of performance throughout the concert. At this concert, Bonzo also 
shines especially in his drum solos with marvelous stereo effects, as well as 
in the very powerful Achilles Last Stand. The recording so vividly and lively 
revives his amazing technique, power and "feel" that no other drummer in the 
world would probably ever be able to attain or surpass for good ... there 
also are some funny moments captured in this recording. On the other note, 
it was at this show, when coming out for the encore, Jimmy slips coming 
forward playing Rock and Roll. He immeadiately gets up with a big grin on 
his face
